<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465781">Master Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1591<br> <font color=#333333>(1/8/03 12:55:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=255.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do I say?</span><hr size=1> I say <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>if </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->you can get your epic done before 60, then do it.  A 55 mage with epic is FAR above any other 55 mage in power.  If you don't see this as viable, then just head for 61.<br>
<br>
I still use my epic in most non-PoP zones.  It is a better tank, more DPS, higher HP and better taunt than the 61 Air pet.  However the 61 air pet works quite well in PoP groups and makes non-epic magician pets much more useful than before.  I think everyone will agree that GV pets aren't going to hold up to much of anything in PoP. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
